{
  "local_port": 48942,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am using a Moto G, and it failed to download the OTA update of Android due to a network error. Now what can I do to get it updated?",
  "response": "If your Moto G failed to download the OTA update due to a network error, you can try the following steps to resolve the issue and successfully update your device:\n\n1. **Check Network Connection:**\n   - Ensure you have a stable internet connection. If you're using Wi-Fi, try moving closer to the router or restarting the router. If you're using mobile data, make sure you have a strong signal.\n\n2. **Retry the Download:**\n   - Go to `Settings` > `System` > `Advanced` > `System updates` and tap on `Check for updates` to try downloading the update again.\n\n3. **Clear Cache:**\n   - Sometimes clearing the cache of the system update app can help.\n   - Go to `Settings` > `Apps & notifications` > `See all apps`. Look for an app related to system updates (it may be called \"Update Services\" or similar). Tap on it, then go to `Storage & cache` and select `Clear cache`.\n\n4. **Free Up Storage:**\n   - Make sure you have enough free storage space for the update. If not, consider deleting unnecessary files or apps.\n   - Go to `Settings` > `Storage` to see usage and free up space if needed.\n\n5. **Restart Your Device:**\n   - Turn off your Moto G and turn it back on. Sometimes a simple restart can resolve glitches.\n\n6. **Safe Mode:**\n   - Boot your device into Safe Mode to ensure no third-party apps are interfering.\n   - Press and hold the power button until you see \"Power off.\" Tap and hold \"Power off\" until you see the option for \"Reboot to safe mode,\" then tap OK.\n\n7. **Manual Installation:**\n   - Check the Moto G support website to see if the update can be downloaded to a computer and installed manually using a USB cable.\n\n8. **Contact Support:**\n   - If you continue to experience issues, you may want to reach out to Motorola\u2019s customer support for further assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully download and install the OTA update on your Moto G.",
